Command line change follow up:                                                                    
   
  1. Keyboard shortcuts not wired in panel context — Cmd+D / Cmd+Shift+D are blocked from 
  reaching PTY in TerminalInstance.tsx, but nothing in the terminal panel catches them to
  call splitTabGroup(). The toolbar buttons work, but keyboard shortcuts are dead in the  
  panel. Tab cycling (Cmd+]/[ or similar) also has no keyboard handler despite cycleTab()
  existing in the store.
  2. No tab context menu — Right-clicking a terminal tab does nothing. Missing: Rename,
  Rename, Close, Close Others. This is a significant UX gap vs VS Code's
  terminal tabs.
  3. Terminal rename has no UI — updateTerminalLabel() exists in the store but is         
  unreachable from any component. No double-click-to-rename on tabs, no F2 shortcut, no   
  context menu entry.
  4. Missing app commands — Only new-terminal and toggle-terminal-panel exist in the      
  AppCommand union. Missing: split-terminal-horizontal, split-terminal-vertical,          
  close-terminal, cycle-terminal-tab, rename-terminal, toggle-terminal-pinned. This means
  the command palette can't invoke these operations either. 
